  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Marketing Manager",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Develop and implement digital marketing strategies to promote electrical products and services</p></li><li><p>Manage and optimize paid advertising campaigns (Google Ads, Facebook, Instagram, etc.)</p></li><li><p>Oversee social media channels, including content planning, posting, and engagement</p></li><li><p>Manage website content, SEO, and product listings to improve traffic and conversions</p></li><li><p>Plan and execute email marketing campaigns and promotional offers</p></li><li><p>Track, analyze, and report on campaign performance using analytics tools</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with sales and store teams to align online promotions with in-store offers</p></li><li><p>Manage digital marketing budget and ensure cost-effective campaigns</p></li><li><p>Stay updated with digital marketing trends and competitor activities in the electrical market</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements & Qualifications</h3><p><p>Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, or a related field (preferred)<br />Proven experience as a Digital Marketing Manager or similar role<br />Strong knowledge of SEO, SEM, social media marketing, and online advertising<br />Experience with e-commerce platforms and product-based marketing<br />Familiarity with tools like Google Analytics, Meta Ads Manager, and email marketing platforms<br />Excellent communication and project management skills<br />Creative mindset with strong analytical abilities<br /><br />Other Information:<br /><br />5.5 workdays a week<br /><br />Able to work in weekends, public holidays</p></p>",
